    h2.heading-large Privacy policy
    p This privacy policy explains why the Ministry of Justice collects personal data when you use the Ask a question service.
    p The policy also explains:
    ul.list.list-bullet
      li how we store this data
      li what we do with it
      li how you can get a copy of the data we have about you
      li how you can complain if you think we’ve done something wrong
    p This service is managed by the Ministry of Justice (MOJ). MOJ is the data controller for the personal information we hold.
    p MOJ collects and processes personal data so that it can safely and securely provide answers to correspondence.
    h3.heading-medium About personal information
    p Personal data is information about you as an individual. It can be your name, address or telephone number.
    p We know how important it is to protect your privacy and to comply with data protection laws. We will keep your personal data safe and will only disclose it where it is lawful to do so, or with your consent.
    h3.heading-medium Types of personal data we process
    p We only process personal data that is relevant for the services we are providing to you. This includes your question, query, feedback and email address. We also collect site-usage information which allows us to see how the service is being used in order to allow us to improve it. This information does not contain any personal data. It includes:
    ul.list.list-bullet
      li your IP address, and details of which version of web browser you used
      li information on how you use the site, using cookies and page tagging techniques to help us improve the website
    p This helps us to:
    ul.list.list-bullet
      li improve the site by monitoring how you use it
      li respond to any feedback you send us, if you’ve asked us to
      li provide you with information about local services if you want it
    p We can’t personally identify you using your site usage data.
    h3.heading-medium Purpose of processing and the lawful basis for the process
    p We collect personal data to enable us to tailor and respond to your correspondence accordingly.
    h3.heading-medium Who the information may be shared with
    p We do not share your information with anyone else.
    h3.heading-medium Details of transfers to third country and safeguards
    p All data collected by this service is stored within the European Economic Area (EEA). However, due to the global nature of the internet, the data sent to and from the database may transit through countries outside of the EEA. Data is not stored in a non-EEA country. Any transfers made will be in full compliance with all aspects of the data protection law.
    h3.heading-medium How long we keep data
    p In the case of Freedom of Information (FOI) requests, data is retained for three years after the last action in accordance with FOI retention policy.
    p In the case of Information Commissioner Reviews, data is destroyed after 5 years from last action.
    p For all other requests, data is retained for two years after the last action.
